Abdomen dark. Tenth tergum (
Figs. 32, 34
) in lateral view subquadrate with rounded distal margin; in dorsal view strongly inflated distally. Tenth sternum (
Figs. 32–33
) strongly sclerotized; in ventral view broad, with proximal margin V–shaped and with tip slightly incised; in lateral view slightly curved dorsad, strongly inflated in distal half.

Eighth sternum subtrapezoidal in lateral view, with distal margin strongly produced posteriorly. Tenth tergum (
Fig. 35
) short and thick with tip acutely pointed. Gonocoxite (
Fig. 35
) membranous, subquadrate, directed dorsad.
